#For a better understanding of our datasets, we name the columns from the variable information found in this website https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/363/facebook+comment+volume+dataset
page_features = ['likes','visitors','daily_interest','category']
derived = ['derived_{}'.format(i) for i in range(1,26)]
essential_features = ['C_total', 'C_last_24h', 'C_last_48h-24h', 'C_release', 'C2-C3']
base_features = ['base_time','post_length','share_count','promotion_status','H_hrs']
weekday = ['Sunday', 'Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday']
base_DT = ['BDT_Sun', 'BDT_Mon', 'BDT_Tue', 'BDT_Wed', 'BDT_Thu', 'BDT_Fri', 'BDT_Sat']
target = ['No_of_Comments_in_H_hours']
cols = page_features+derived+essential_features+base_features+weekday+base_DT+target

API¶

In [ ]:
#An attempt at implementing API, we unfortunately could not achieve it

"""

from http.server import BaseHTTPRequestHandler, HTTPServer
import json
import webbrowser
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
import numpy as np

class MyHandler(BaseHTTPRequestHandler):
    model = LinearRegression()

    def _send_response(self, response_code=200, content_type='text/html', content=None):
        self.send_response(response_code)
        self.send_header('Content-type', content_type)
        self.end_headers()

        if content:
            self.wfile.write(content.encode('utf-8'))

    def calculate_metrics(self, X, y):
        predictions = self.model.predict(X)
        accuracy = self.model.score(X, y)
        mse = mean_squared_error(y, predictions)
        return accuracy, mse

    def do_GET(self):
        if self.path == '/api':
            accuracies = []
            mses = []
            for i in range(1, 11):
                tX = globals()[f'tX{i}']
                ty = globals()[f'ty{i}']
                accuracy, mse = self.calculate_metrics(tX, ty)
                accuracies.append(accuracy)
                mses.append(mse)

            avg_accuracy = np.mean(accuracies)
            avg_mse = np.mean(mses)

            data = {
                'message': 'Hello, this is your API!',
                'average_accuracy': avg_accuracy,
                'average_mse': avg_mse
            }
            json_data = json.dumps(data)

            html_response = f"""
            <html>
            <head><title>API Page</title></head>
            <body>
                <h1>Hello, this is your API!</h1>
                <p>Average Accuracy: {avg_accuracy}</p>
                <p>Average MSE: {avg_mse}</p>
            </body>
            </html>
            """
            self._send_response(content_type='text/html', content=html_response)

        else:
            self._send_response(response_code=404, content='Not Found')

def run_server(port=8080, open_browser=True):
    server_address = ('', port)
    httpd = HTTPServer(server_address, MyHandler)
    print(f'Starting server on port {port}...')

    if open_browser:
        webbrowser.open(f'http://localhost:{port}/api')

    httpd.serve_forever()

run_server(port=8080, open_browser=True)
